8) (Optional) Appendix — Quick Q&A Snippets
Use these as ready‑made flashcards for your chatbot:
•	Q: What does a rheostat do?
A: It’s a variable resistor used to control current.
•	Q: How should a voltmeter be connected in a circuit?
A: In parallel across the two points of interest.
•	Q: Why should an ammeter have very low resistance?
A: To avoid dropping voltage and to measure current accurately when placed in series.
•	Q: Where is a slip ring induction motor preferred?
A: Applications needing high starting torque or better speed control.
•	Q: What is the role of a circuit breaker?
A: It interrupts current automatically when a fault occurs.
                                                    
